I'm reviewing the plumbing service I received from Mike's Plumbing and Electric.  They were dispatched via my home warranty company.  They responded quickly to my issue, showed up on time, and called me when they were enroute.  The technician was polite, courteous, and took the time to let me walk him through the issue we were having with our bathtub.  He fixed the problem promptly and even gave me a few pointers to help me prevent similar issues in the future.

I've seen a few bad reviews from people based on their "home warranty" and their repair not being covered.  Whether you dispatch a plumber, electrician, or AC specialist, they can only cover items that your home warranty company lets them cover, based on your contract (that you picked).  People should read their contracts first before taking their frustrations out on a local business.  Cheaper home warranties cover less items, go figure.

googleReviewsBySlug.json.responseFromOwnerText:
In reference to this customers complaint:
She has a home warranty company that took a week or so to send a denial on the replacement of the valve for her. Evidently she doesn't have fixture coverage and the present valve is discontinued, yet the warranty company demanded we track down a part. They are the ones  supposed to communicate all this with the customers, per our contract. After lots of searching, off the clock on our own time not work time, we were finally able to track down a cartridge replacement from an individual. At that point, we can't buy because we have to send another bid to the warranty company to see if they would approve it. After a day or so, we finally get an approval email and we ordered the part which was stated to take 2 weeks to arrive. Warranty company has been aware of everything. Thus, this is an unfair review being that we have handled our end exactly how our contract states we are to. Also, the part is due in tomorrow morning, so we will see.
